cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper deals with the task of autonomously unloading boxes from trucks using a robotic system, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed framework involves motion planning, belief space planning, decision-making, and execution, which are all related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The system also needs to account for imperfect information about the boxes, which could involve computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the real-time execution module involves combining decision-making with motion planning, which could be related to control systems (cs.SY).
